---
/**
 * Join Our Team Page
 * ==================
 * Careers and job opportunities page.
 */

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Join Our Team"
  description="Career opportunities at APP Legal Services. We are looking for talented candidates who are passionate about the legal profession."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Careers</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="page-title">Join Our Team</h1>
      <p class="page-update">
        Build Your Career with Experienced Legal Professionals
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="legal-content section-padding">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <article class="legal-article">
          <p class="intro">
            APP Legal Services, founded by a legal practitioner with over 22
            years of experience, is expanding its professional network and
            invites enthusiastic, dedicated, and career-oriented individuals to
            work with us.
            <br /><br />
            We are looking for talented candidates who are passionate about the legal
            profession and committed to delivering quality legal services to clients.
          </p>

          <h2>Opportunities Available For</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Junior Advocates</li>
            <li>Associate Advocates</li>
            <li>Legal Consultants</li>
            <li>Law Graduates</li>
            <li>Legal Researchers</li>
            <li>Paralegals</li>
            <li>Interns (Law Students)</li>
            <li>Administrative and Client Support Executives</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Desired Qualities</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Strong communication and drafting skills</li>
            <li>Professional ethics and integrity</li>
            <li>Willingness to learn and grow</li>
            <li>Client-oriented approach</li>
            <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li>
            <li>Knowledge of legal research and documentation</li>
            <li>
              Basic computer proficiency and familiarity with legal software
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>What We Offer</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Practical exposure to diverse legal matters</li>
            <li>Mentorship and professional guidance</li>
            <li>
              Opportunity to work on litigation and non-litigation assignments
            </li>
            <li>Professional growth and skill development</li>
            <li>Dynamic and collaborative working environment</li>
            <li>Performance-based opportunities and advancement</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Terms & Conditions</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Submission of an application does not guarantee selection or
              engagement.
            </li>
            <li>
              Selection shall be based on qualifications, experience,
              suitability, and interview performance.
            </li>
            <li>
              The organization reserves the right to accept or reject any
              application without assigning any reason.
            </li>
            <li>
              Candidates may be required to undergo an interview, assessment, or
              probation period.
            </li>
            <li>
              Engagement terms, remuneration, responsibilities, and working
              arrangements shall be communicated separately to selected
              candidates.
            </li>
            <li>
              All information submitted by applicants must be accurate and
              complete. Any misrepresentation may result in rejection or
              termination of engagement.
            </li>
            <li>
              Candidates shall maintain strict confidentiality regarding client
              information, office records, and professional matters.
            </li>
            <li>
              Professional conduct, integrity, and compliance with applicable
              laws and ethical standards are mandatory.
            </li>
            <li>
              APP Legal Services reserves the right to modify, amend, or
              withdraw any vacancy or engagement opportunity at its discretion.
            </li>
            <li>
              By submitting an application, the candidate agrees to the above
              terms and conditions.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Grow with Us</h2>
          <p>
            At APP Legal Services, we believe in professional excellence,
            continuous learning, and client-focused legal solutions. If you are
            looking to build a meaningful career in the legal field, we welcome
            your application.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong
              >Apply Today and Become Part of Our Growing Legal Team.</strong
            >
          </p>
          <h2>How to Apply</h2>
          <!-- <p>Interested candidates may submit their:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Updated Resume/Curriculum Vitae</li>
            <li>Educational Qualifications</li>
            <li>Experience Details (if any)</li>
            <li>Contact Information</li>
          </ul> -->

          <div class="contact-box">
            <p>
              <strong>APP Legal Services</strong><br />
              Founder: Advocate with 22+ Years of Legal Practice<br /><br />
              <strong>Email:</strong> applegalservices26@gmail.com<br />
              <strong>Mobile:</strong> +91-9152109228
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3>Submit Your Application</h3>
          <p>
            Please send your updated Resume/CV along with a brief cover letter
            directly to our email address:
            <strong
              ><a href="mailto:applegalservices26@gmail.com"
                >applegalservices26@gmail.com</a
              ></strong
            >
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--color-primary-900) 0%,
      var(--color-primary-700) 100%
    );
    color: white;
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }
  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-500);
  }
  .breadcrumb span {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  }
  .breadcrumb span:last-child {
    color: var(--color-accent-500);
  }

  .page-title {
    color: white;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-update {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .legal-content {
    background: var(--surface-primary);
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-body);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .legal-article h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-light);
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  /* Global dark mode override for headings */
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .legal-article h2 {
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .legal-article p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-article ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-article li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .contact-box {
    background: var(--surface-body);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-500);
  }

  .contact-box p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }
</style>
